HEADWORD: Gyracanthus
<hw>Gyr`a*can"thus</hw> <pr>(j⟦icr⟧r`⟦adot⟧*k⟦acr⟧n"th⟦ucr⟧s)</pr>,
<pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL., fr. Gr. <grk>gyro`s</grk> round +
<grk>'a`kanqa</grk> spine.]</ety> <fld>(Paleon.)</fld> <def>A genus of
fossil fishes, found in Devonian and carboniferous strata; -- so named
from their round, sculptured spines.</def>⟦br⟧
